Package: EpiAwareR
Type: Package
Title: R Interface to the EpiAware Compositional Infectious Disease Modelling Framework
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Sebastian", "Funk", email = "sebastian.funk@lshtm.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides an R interface to the Julia-based EpiAware compositional
    infectious disease modelling framework. EpiAwareR enables R users to build
    flexible epidemiological models by composing reusable components for latent
    processes, infection dynamics, and observation models without requiring
    Julia expertise.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    JuliaCall (>= 0.17.0),
    tibble,
    posterior,
    ggplot2,
    checkmate
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    readr,
    bayesplot
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
SystemRequirements: Julia (>= 1.9.0), Julia packages: EpiAware, Turing, Distributions
URL: https://github.com/sbfnk/EpiAware
BugReports: https://github.com/sbfnk/EpiAware/issues
